Asked several times by Sen. Herb Kohl, D-Wis., about women's right to endtheir pregnancies, Thomas said, "Whether or not I have a view is irrelevant.";

President Bush, asked at a news conference whether Thomas' claim not to have an opinion on abortion is credible, answered, "That's a question for the Senate to decide."
They also have voiced skepticism about his backing away from stands he took in past writings and speeches.; Committee Chairman Joseph Biden, D-Del., began to show signs of exasperation today during spirited questioning about the nominee's views on "natural law," a theory that certain rights exist independent of written law.; At one point, Biden accused Thomas of using "tortuous logic."
